The paper introduces new information theoretic measures for communication complexity in a multi-party peer-to-peer setting, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on lower bounds for communication complexity, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions private computation, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as possible sub-categories.
